<FIRST>r w PM-NorthCharges     02-01 0141</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-North Charges,140</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-North Trial Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of the 12 felony charges against
former National Security Council aide Oliver L. North. All carry
five-year prison terms and fines up to $250,000 except as noted.
   Obstruction of Congress in Sept. and Oct. 1985.
   False statements to Congress on Sept. 5, 1985.
   False statements to Congress on Sept. 12, 1985.
   False statements to Congress on Oct. 7, 1985
   Obstruction of Congress in Aug. 1986.
   Obstruction of Congress in Nov. 1986.
   Obstruction of a presidential inquiry in Nov. 1986.
   False statements on Nov. 23, 1986.
   Destroying or falsifying government documents, three-year
imprisonment and $250,000 fine.
   Receipt of an illegal gratuity, two-year imprisonment and
$250,000 fine.
   Conversion of traveler's checks to personal use, 10-year
imprisonment, $250,000 fine.
   Conspiracy to defraud the Treasury and the Internal Revenue
Service.
