<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Philippines-Drunks     02-01 0130</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Philippines-Drunks,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mayor Nips Noon Time Nipping In The Bud</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mayor Gemiliano Lopez has nipped
noon-time nipping by revoking the liquor licenses of restaurants
near city hall after complaints that municipal workers were
returning from lunch breaks drunk.
   Lopez's order, issued Tuesday, canceled the liquor licenses of
about 30 restaurants within 200 yards of city hall. Lopez ordered
officials not to issue new licenses to restaurants on three major
streets near his office.
   The mayor also issued a directive warning city employees that he
would not tolerate alcohol abuse.
   A city ordinance already banned liquor sales within 200 yards of
public buildings, churches and schools but officials said the
Department of Tourism had exempted establishments near city hall
because they ostensibly catered mostly to tourists.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
