<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A British soldier died early
today from wounds sustained in a bomb blast outside a Belfast pub,
police said. A second soldier suffered slight injuries.
   The outlawed Irish Republican Army, which is fighting British
rule in the province, claimed responsibility for Tuesday night's
explosion in a coded message to news organizations.
   A press officer at police headquarters said infantryman Pvt.
Nicholas David Peacock died after a bomb exploded as his joint
army-police foot patrol passed a pub in the Falls Road section of
