counts of manslaughter in the men's deaths, said the results support
the policeman's contention that Lloyd was trying to run him down.
   On Tuesday, the 11-member review panel set up by the city to
review the slaying was picketed by members of the black organization
People United to Lead the Struggle for Equality because five police
officers are on the board.
   ``That disallows it, we feel, to function as a citizens'
independent review panel,'' said PULSE spokesman Van Eubanks.
   Annie Goodman, one of five black Overtown residents on the board,
pleaded for more time. ``Don't doubt us before we take a step,'' she
said.
