<HEAD>Man Steals Bus, Killed By Police</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto BX3</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man stole an empty Greyhound bus and smashed into
13 cars, including four police cruisers, before he was killed in a
hail of gunfire while speeding toward police officers, authorities
said.
   ``It was the only way to stop him,'' said police spokesman James
Jordan. ``The bus came to rest on the top of a vehicle.''
   The bus apparently was stolen Tuesday from New Bedford, about 50
miles south of Boston, Jordan said. The man drove it through several
Boston neighborhoods, hitting a house in addition to the vehicles.
   The man, who remained unidentified today, died at Boston City
Hospital with gunshot wounds to the chest, hospital spokesman Mark
Douville said.
   The number of shots fired and the names of the officers involved
were not released.
   One officer suffered an injured hand, and two officers were
treated for chest pains, but there were no serious injuries, Jordan
said.
