<DOCNO> AP890201-0133 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-02-01-89 1339EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r w BC-PayRaise-List 3Takes   02-01 0528</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Pay Raise-List, 3 Takes,</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of responses by House members to
a survey conducted Jan. 13-31 by groups opposed to the proposed pay
raise.
   The survey was conducted by Public Citizen, a consumer advocacy
group founded by Ralph Nader; the National Taxpayers Union, a
non-partisan organization of fiscal conservatives; and Coalitions
for America, a conservative organization headed by activist Paul
Weyrich.
   The 50 percent pay raise for members of Congress and top federal
officials becomes law Feb. 8 unless both houses of Congress vote to
stop it.
   The survey question was: If President Reagan's proposed 50
percent pay raise comes up for a vote, how would the representative
vote?
   A ``yes'' vote is shown here as Y.
   A ``no'' vote is shown as N.
   A ``no response'' is shown as NR.
   Undecided is shown as U.
   There are two vacancies in the 435-member House.
</TEXT>
