<HEAD>Mother Charged With Murder in Baby's Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BURNSVILLE, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman was charged Wednesday with
murder in the dehydration death of her 6-month-old daughter,
authorities say was left alone for a week while the mother went on
vacation.
   Peggy Ann Barsness, 22, of Burnsville was charged in Dakota
County District Court with one count each of second- and
third-degree murder in the death of Kirsten Barsness, said County
Attorney James Backstrom. District Judge Robert Carolan set bail at
$200,000.
