found the child dead earlier that morning after returning from
visiting a boyfriend in California. She said she had arranged for a
baby sitter, but was unable to provide the person's last name, phone
number or address, police Lt. Fred Rau said Tuesday.
   ``We've been able to find no information that she made any
arrangements to have the baby cared for while it was home alone,''
Rau said.
