<HEAD>Mebane Named Newspaper Division President At Multimedia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREENVILLE, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   William deBerniere Mebane, publisher of
The Greenville News and Greenville Piedmont, on Wednesday was named
president of Multimedia Inc.'s newspaper division, company officials
said.
   Mebane, 40, succeeds Donald J. Barhyte, who is resigning.
   ``He (Mebane) has exhibited leadership throughout the 18 years he
has been with the company,'' said Walter E. Bartlett, president and
chief executive of Multimedia.
   Barhyte, 52, said he was resigning ``for personal reasons,'' and
will continue to be associated with Multimedia in an advisory
capacity. He also will leave the company's board, he said.
   Mebane, who is vice president of the newspaper division as well
as publisher, becomes the division's president on March 1.
   Mebane joined Multimedia in 1971. He also has been assistant
business manager, business manager and general manager.
   Multimedia is a diversified media communications company which
publishes 14 daily newspapers in South Carolina, North Carolina,
Florida, Georgia, Alabama, Ohio, Virginia and Tennessee.
   The company also owns 40 non-daily newspapers, four television
and seven radio stations, operates more than 100 cable franchises in
four states, and produces and syndicates television programming,
including the Phil Donahue and Sally Jessy Raphael shows.
