<FIRST>r a AM-People-Madonna-Penn     02-01 0333</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Madonna-Penn,0342</SECOND>
<HEAD>Madonna Files Divorce Petition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress-singer Madonna and estranged
husband Sean Penn have agreed on a division of property and filed a
petition for divorce, court records show.
   The Los Angeles County Superior Court petition to dissolve the
stormy three-year marriage cited irreconcilable differences as the
reason for the split, and seeks restoration of the singer's former
name, Madonna Ciccone.
   It also said community property and financial obligations shared
by the couple ``have been disposed of by written agreement.'' No
details were disclosed in the two-page petition filed Jan. 25.
   Madonna publicist Liz Rosenberg said last week that Penn would
get the couple's Malibu home and the singer would keep the New York
apartment. Madonna bought a $2.9 million Hollywood Hills home
earlier this month.
   Penn's attorney, Marcy Rosenblum, declined to comment, and
publicist Lois Smith didn't return telephone calls Wednesday.
   It is the second time the sultry songstress has taken steps to
end her 1985 marriage to Penn. She first filed a Superior Court
divorce petition in 1987, but later withdrew it.
   The latest divorce action follows a Dec. 28 incident in which Los
Angeles County Sheriff's Department deputies were called to the
couple's Malibu home after the hot-tempered Penn allegedly beat
Madonna. No charges were filed.
   Madonna rose to fame with her hits ``Borderline'' and ``Like a
Virgin,'' and is perhaps best known by the title of another song,
``Material Girl.'' She starred in the movies ``Desperately Seeking
Susan'' and ``Shanghai Surprise,'' a box office dud co-starring Penn.
   Penn rose to stardom in the movie ``Fast Times at Ridgemont
High'' and went on to appear in ``Taps,'' ``The Falcon and the
Snowman'' and ``Colors.''
   Penn served more than half of a 60-day jail term in 1987 for
violating parole by punching a movie extra during filming of the
movie ``Colors.'' He was on probation at the time for punching a man
he accused of trying to kiss Madonna in a nightclub in April 1986.
</TEXT>
