<HEAD>Three-Year-Old Used As Shield In Gun Battle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 3-year-old boy used as a shield during a gun
battle Wednesday was shot and seriously wounded, and police said
they later arrested a wounded man who plucked up the toddler when
the shooting started.
   The child was shot in the left arm, but the bullet traveled to
his chest, said Sgt. John Clifford, a police spokesman.
   ``The child was an innocent bystander,'' said Detective Joseph
McConville.
   The tot, whose name was not released, was in serious but stable
condition at Brookdale Hospital ater the 12:35 p.m. gunfight in the
Cypress Housing Project, in the tough East New York section of
Brookly, Clifford said.
   The toddler was with his mother, who was pushing another baby in
a stroller when at least three men began shooting at each other, but
the reasons behind the gun battle were not known, Clifford said.
   Eric Casseus, 18, who was being chased, ``picked up a
three-year-old boy and used him as a shield,'' Clifford said.
   Casseus was shot in the left foot and was treated and discharged
from Brookdale, and was charged with first-degree assault and
unlawful imprisonment, police said.
