<FIRST>r f BC-EEC-Inflation     02-01 0090</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-EEC-Inflation,0096</SECOND>
<HEAD>Inflation Up 4.4 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Inflation in the 12-nation European
Community averaged 4.4 percent in 1988, up from 2.6 percent the
previous year, the trading bloc reported Wednesday.
   The EEC statistical office, Eurostat, said inflation ranged from
a low of 1.2 percent in Holland to a high of 14 percent in Greece.
   The average rate equaled that of the United States, but was far
higher than the 0.9 percent in Japan, Eurostat said.
   The EEC's monthly inflation rose 0.3 percent in December, it said.
</TEXT>
