<HEAD>Commodore Fills President's Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST CHESTER, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mehdi Ali, managing director of Dillon,
Read &amp; Co. Inc., New York, is the new president of Commodore
International Ltd., Commodore chairman Irving Gould announced
Wednesday.
   Ali has been a special advisor to Commodore for the last three
years and in August was elected to the board of directors. He has
been with Dillon, Read since 1984 and served as vice president at
PepsiCo Inc. and General Motors Corp. the previous eight years.
   Commodore makes and sells personal computers.
   Gould said Ali has been working with the restructuring of
Commodore and will ``expand the role he has been playing in the
restructuring (of the company) into a major competitor in the
microcomputer industry.''
   The job of president has been vacant for two years. Gould has
been both board chairman and chief executive officer.
