<SECOND>BC-Earns-Grace,0170</SECOND>
<HEAD>W.R. Grace Posts Fourth-Quarter Profit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   W.R. Grace &amp; Co. said Wednesday its
fourth-quarter net income rose 51 percent, helped by strong
performances in all four of its business segments.
   For the three-month period ended Dec. 31, the New York-based
holding company said its after-tax profit totaled $75.5 million, or
88 cents a share, up from $50.1 million, or 59 cents a share in the
1987 quarter. Revenue rose 26.6 percent to $1.65 billion from $1.3
billion.
   For all of 1988, the W.R. Grace said its net income rose 35
percent to $233.6 million, or $2.75 a share, from $173.1 million, or
$2.03 a share. Revenue for 1988 rose 28 percent to $5.79 billion
from $4.52 billion.
   ``There's no question that all of Grace's business lines are on
solid footing and growing steadily,'' said J. Peter Grace, chief
executive.
   The company's businesses include chemicals, energy, health care
and specialty businesses, such as cocoa processing and software
distribution.
</TEXT>
