over-the-counter market. MCI posted substantially higher
fourth-quarter operating earnings.
   As measured by Wilshire Associates' index of more than 5,000
actively traded stocks, the market lost $0.37 billion, or 0.01
percent, in value.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks
slipped .16 to 166.47.
