<FIRST>r f AM-RJRNabisco     02-01 0174</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-RJR Nabisco,0180</SECOND>
<HEAD>Delaware Court Dismisses Shareholder Suits Against RJR Nabisco</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Delaware Chancery Court has dismissed nine
shareholder suits filed in an attempt to block the $24.53 billion
takeover of RJR Nabisco Inc. by Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &amp; Co., RJR
Nabisco said Wednesday.
   The suits generally claimed that RJR Nabisco's board violated its
fiduciary responsibilities during bidding for the company by
Kohlberg Kravis and a management group led by president F. Ross
Johnson.
   The lawsuits were some of the last obstacles to Kohlberg Kravis'
$109-per-share offer for RJR Nabisco, set to expire at midnight
Monday.
   Earlier this week, Kohlberg Kravis announced it had reached
agreement with Federal Trade Commission staff on the sale of some
RJR Nabisco food products or Beatrice Cos. products to satisfy
antitrust concerns. KKR won Beatrice in a $6.1 billion deal in 1986.
   Still pending are lawsuits in New York by disgruntled
bondholders, including ITT Corp. and Metropolitan Life, who are
concerned that the value of their bonds declined during the bidding
late last year.
